title: MECHANOGRAPHICS
subtitle: Visualization of free body diagrams
place: KJ SOMAIYA COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING, MUMBAI
description:
BE(Senior) project
A mechanics based problem is taken as input in the form of English sentence. Which is later processed using Stanford CoreNLP to render a free body diagram.

title: Version Control System
description: Copies an existing repository into a destination folder of user's specified name. Exit application from the command prompt using 'exit' command. Non-valid words (in this case, only 'create' command is accepted) are rejected.

title: Low Power Image Recognition
description:
Objective of this project was to reduce the time required by a model to identify an image and test it on mobile phones. The project was inspired by the Low-Power Image Recognition Challenge by IEEE 2018. ImageNet data was collected and trained on several neural network models. Several available models such as, AlexNet, MobileNet. were modified and trained on various datasets.

Objective of this project was to reduce the time required by a model to identify an image and test it on mobile phones, inspired by the Low-Power Image Recognition Challenge by IEEE 2018. ImageNet data was collected and trained on several neural network models including AlexNet, MobileNet.

title: Graph DB Exploration
description: Experimented various BigData Platform like AWS, Map Reduce, Apache Spark, and Graph DB tools like Neo4J, MongoDB, and GraphQL. Applied graph DB using Neo4J to a project for the professor's research, on neurons and its activation based on the human emotions.
